Company.Name: Baskin-Robbins
Executive.First.Name: Mario
Executive.Last.Name: Ruffo
Professional.Title: NA
Executive.Title: Owner
Company.Description: Founded in 1945, Baskin-Robbins is one of the world s largest chains of ice-cream specialty stores. The chain operates more than 6,000 retail shops in over 30 countries, including the United States, Japan, Korea, Australia and the Middle East. Its stores offer ice cream in nearly 1,000 flavors, including vanilla, chocolate, strawberry and mint chocolate chip. The chain s stores also sell a variety of cakes, pies, beverages, sundaes and frozen desserts. Its stores provide food items under the Cappuccino Blast, Jamoca, Oreo, Bright Choices and World Class brands. In addition, Baskin-Robbins stores offer gift certificates, discount options and reward programs. The chain maintains partnerships with The Hershey Company and MARS, as well as provides more than 300 million customers each year. It supports several community-based organizations and fundraising events. The chain has been recognized as one of the leading ice-cream companies by Entrepreneur Magazine. Baskin-Robbins is a part of Dunkin' Brands, which is a chain that offers coffee, doughnuts and bagels.

Company.Name: Costco
Executive.First.Name: Eric
Executive.Last.Name: Ward
Professional.Title: NA
Executive.Title: Site Manager
Company.Description: With sales revenue of more than $60 billion, Costco Wholesale Corporation is one of the leading, international chains of membership warehouses in the world. Operating under the Costco trade name, its warehouses offer branded merchandise at lower prices than conventional wholesale and retail outlets. The members-only warehouse stores offer one of the largest product categories under a single roof. Its warehouses carry groceries, appliances, television and media items, automotive supplies, tires, toys, hardware, sporting goods, jewelry, watches, cameras, books, apparel, health and beauty aids, furniture, and office equipment and supplies. Costco offers business, gold star and executive membership options. It has more than 500 warehouses with average size of over 120,000 square feet. Costco Wholesale Corporation also operates self-service gasoline stations at various locations in the United States and Canada. Costco Wholesale Industries, a division of the company, operates special food packaging, optical laboratories, jewelry distribution and meat processing businesses.

Company.Name: Denny's
Professional.Title: NA
Company.Description: Dennys is Americas Diner. Where guests have come for over 60 years to relax and enjoy good, hearty meals at reasonable prices. Open 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, Dennys restaurants serve classic breakfast around the clock as well as craveable salads, hand-pressed burgers and homestyle dinners. Our menu is broad yet familiar, which makes us a great place to take the kids and family. And now, for a limited time, you can celebrate our #BigBurgerBash, featuring our new, bolder burger line-up with juicy 100% beef patties piled high with fresh ingredients, bold flavors, melty cheeses and premium toppings.With over 1700 locations worldwide, including the U.S. and in more than 11 foreign countries and territories, Dennys is always ready to serve you. Welcome to Americas Diner.

Executive.Last.Name: Steiner
Professional.Title: NA
Executive.Title: General Mgr
Company.Description: Founded in 1957, Food Lion is one of the largest supermarket chains in the United States. It operates more than 1,200 supermarkets, directly and through affiliated entities, under the names of Food Lion, Bloom, Bottom Dollar, Harveys and Reid s. The company is a part of Brussels-based Delhaize Group, which operates food supermarkets in North America, Europe and Southeast Asia. Food Lion s stores offer nationally and regionally advertised branded products, as well as private-label products. It employs more than 70,000 associates and sells over 28,000 different products. The company is active in various community and charitable causes, including the Children s Miracle Network, America s Second Harvest, Easter Seals, the United Way, the American Red Cross and local schools. Headquartered in Salisbury, N.C., the company maintains a presence in Apex, N.C.

Company.Description: Founded in 1957, Food Lion is one of the largest supermarket chains in the United States. It operates more than 1,200 supermarkets, directly and through affiliated entities, under the names of Food Lion, Bloom, Bottom Dollar, Harveys and Reid s. The company is a part of Brussels-based Delhaize Group, which operates food supermarkets in North America, Europe and Southeast Asia. Food Lion s stores offer nationally and regionally advertised branded products, as well as private-label products. It employs more than 70,000 associates and sells over 28,000 different products. The company is active in various community and charitable causes, including the Children s Miracle Network, America s Second Harvest, Easter Seals, the United Way, the American Red Cross and local schools. Headquartered in Salisbury, N.C., the company maintains a presence in Garner, N.C.

Executive.Last.Name: Williams
Professional.Title: NA
Executive.Title: General Mgr
Company.Description: Founded in 1957, Food Lion is one of the largest supermarket chains in the United States. It operates more than 1,200 supermarkets, directly and through affiliated entities, under the names of Food Lion, Bloom, Bottom Dollar, Harveys and Reid s. The company is a part of Brussels-based Delhaize Group, which operates food supermarkets in North America, Europe and Southeast Asia. Food Lion s stores offer nationally and regionally advertised branded products, as well as private-label products. It employs more than 70,000 associates and sells over 28,000 different products. The company is active in various community and charitable causes, including the Children s Miracle Network, America s Second Harvest, Easter Seals, the United Way, the American Red Cross and local schools. Headquartered in Salisbury, N.C., the company maintains a presence in Smithfield, N.C.

Company.Description: Foster's Market is a restaurant that maintains locations in Durham and Chapel Hill, N.C. The restaurant s menu includes a variety of soups, salads, pizzas, sandwiches, side dishes and beverages. It serves grilled salmon, beef, chicken breast, lasagna, pork loin and macaroni. The restaurant offers crab cakes, flautas, chicken strips and steamed shrimp. Foster's Market features a selection of sauces and jellies. The restaurant provides catering services for holiday parties, birthdays, receptions, corporate luncheons, company picnics and business meetings. It offers corporate gifts, cookbooks and online recipes. The restaurant publishes a newsletter that provides updates on upcoming events. Foster's Market additionally offers promotional meal packages and gift cards in several denominations.

Company.Description: In 1936, W. T. Harris opened his first grocery store in Charlotte, N.C. Meanwhile, Willis L. Teeter and his brother, Paul, opened their first Teeter's Food Mart in 1939. In 1960, Harris Super Markets and Teeter's Food Marts officially merged to form Harris Teeter. It is a wholly owned subsidiary of Ruddick Corporation. Harris Teeter operates a chain of food markets in North Carolina, South Carolina, Virginia, Georgia, Tennessee and Florida. The company operates more than 150 retail stores and various grocery, frozen food and perishable distribution centers. It offers a range of food items, including meat, seafood and produce. Harris Teeter organizes a fresh foods program that includes more than 800 bakery and deli products and offers daily samples to its customers. In addition, the company operates several Hunter Farms milk and ice cream facilities in North Carolina. Its VIC program provides special savings and benefits, as well as rewards and free groceries. In addition, the company provides weekly specials and in-store rewards. Harris Teeter employs more than 18,000 employees. Headquartered in Matthews, N.C., it maintains a presence in Cary, N.C.

It has several locations in Raleigh, N.C.

Company.Name: Harris Teeter
Executive.First.Name: Charles
Executive.Last.Name: Brame
Professional.Title: NA
Executive.Title: General Mgr
Company.Description: In 1936, W. T. Harris opened his first grocery store in Charlotte, N.C. Meanwhile, Willis L. Teeter and his brother, Paul, opened their first Teeter's Food Mart in 1939. In 1960, Harris Super Markets and Teeter's Food Marts officially merged to form Harris Teeter. It is a wholly owned subsidiary of Ruddick Corporation. Harris Teeter operates a chain of food markets in North Carolina, South Carolina, Virginia, Georgia, Tennessee and Florida. The company operates more than 150 retail stores and various grocery, frozen food and perishable distribution centers. It offers a range of food items, including meat, seafood and produce. Harris Teeter organizes a fresh foods program that includes more than 800 bakery and deli products and offers daily samples to its customers. In addition, the company operates several Hunter Farms milk and ice cream facilities in North Carolina. Its VIC program provides special savings and benefits, as well as rewards and free groceries. In addition, the company provides weekly specials and in-store rewards. Harris Teeter employs more than 18,000 employees. Headquartered in Matthews, N.C., it maintains a location in Wake Forest, N.C.

Company.Name: Krispy Krunchy Chicken
Professional.Title: NA
Company.Description: Krispy Krunchy Foods offers a quick-serve restaurant concept with more than 1700 retail locations in 35 states. Established in 1989 in Lafayette, LA, we have over 70 combined years of experience in the c-store/ foodservice industry. We feature Cajun-style chicken (bone-in and tenders) which is always fresh never frozen and fried in zero trans fat oil. The menu also includes signature dishes of Krispy, Original and Cajun Sweet & Sour Wings; Cajun tenders; Red Beans and Rice; Jambalaya; Boudin Bites (Cajun rice balls); Krispy Shrimp and Fish; and Honey Butter Biscuits. We serve the convenience store, restaurant and supermarket industries. Krispy Krunchy Chicken specializes in remodeling, re-design, and construction planning. The branded look includes a full graphics package layout, branded paper goods, 20 proprietary branded food items, design and scale drawings. The program may also be co-branded with existing food programs and use existing onsite equipment. Krispy Krunchy provides complete training and support programsTake a look at the HOTTEST chicken concept in America!

Company.Name: Kroger
Executive.First.Name: Karla
Executive.Last.Name: Langworthy
Professional.Title: NA
Executive.Title: General Mgr
Company.Description: In 1883, Barney Kroger, with only $372, opened a grocery store in downtown Cincinnati. More than 120 years later, as the supermarket business has evolved into a variety of formats aimed at satisfying the ever-changing needs of shoppers, Kroger has grown to over 2,500 stores in 31 states under two-dozen banners and annual sales of more than $66 billion. Today, Kroger ranks as one of the nation s largest retailers. Kroger has pioneered many innovations in the supermarket industry. During the 1930s, it was the first grocery chain to monitor product quality and test foods. In 1972, Kroger became the first grocery retailer in America to test an electronic scanner. It was installed in a store in suburban Cincinnati. Technology plays an important role in Kroger s store operations, with more than 1,600 Kroger stores offering self-checkout. Kroger spans many states with store formats that include grocery and multidepartment stores, convenience stores and mall jewelry stores. Among the brands it operates are Fred Meyer, Ralph s, Fry s, Baker s, Food4Less, KwikStop and Tom Thumb. Kroger is headquartered in Cincinnati, and maintains a presence in Apex, N.C.

It's always free to join and you'll earn redeemable points right away with your first purchase. We've got the widest range of vitamins, minerals, sports nutrition supplements and more to meet every body's needs no matter where they might be on their personal journey to wellness. We make it a priority to offer an array of products as exciting and diverse as the customers who shop with us.

Company.Name: Weaver Street Market
Executive.First.Name: Ruffin
Executive.Last.Name: Slater
Professional.Title: NA
Executive.Title: General Mgr
Company.Description: Weaver Street Market is a worker- and consumer-owned cooperative that deals in natural and organic food. It also operates a restaurant, Panzanella, which hosts regular fundraising events for local nonprofit organizations. Panzanella serves gourmet pizzas, grilled sandwiches, homemade pastas and biscotti, plum mascarpone crostata and martinis. Weaver Street Market recycles more than 15 different waste streams, such as corrugated and waxed cardboards, metal cans, plastic bottles, glass, paper, packing peanuts, plastic bags, small wooden packing crates, cooking oil and food waste for compost. Weaver Street Market also provides olives, peppers, capers, spreads, roasted tomatoes and chocolates. In addition, it offers a variety of snacks, including granola, chips, soups, bagels, cereals, snack bars, sodas, juices and cookies. Weaver Street Market maintains various locations in North Carolina, including Carrboro and Chapel Hill.

Company.Description: The Pantry, headquartered in Sanford, N.C., is one of the leading independent convenience store operators in the United States. The Company operates more than 1,400 stores under different names, including Kangaroo Express, Golden Gallon, Cowboys, Handy Way, Quick Stop, Zip Mart, Fast Lane, Big K, Depot, Mini Mart, and Lil Champ Food Store. The Pantry also produces soft drinks and food items, and markets them under the brand name of Celeste and Kangaroo. The stores offer a wide range of merchandise and services, such as gasoline, coffee shops, beverages, candy, magazines, and tobacco products. The Pantry owns and operates retail stores throughout the United States, including Louisiana, Mississippi, Alabama, Georgia, Florida, Tennessee, Kentucky, Indiana, Virginia, North Carolina and South Carolina.
